Description: The Fender Custom Shop 1963 Relic Telecaster takes you back to the early years of one of modern music's most electrifying decades. Its alder body comes in Three-Color Sunburst, Olympic White and Blue Ice Metallic lacquer Relic finishes, with signature Telecaster snap and sparkle coming from dual American Vintage '64 Telecaster pickups with three-way switching and Fender's Greasebucket (TM) tone circuit, which rolls of highs without reducing gain. Other premium features include a quartersawn maple neck with a comfortable mid-'60s oval "C" profile, 9.5" radius "round-laminated" rosewood fingerboard with 21 narrow jumbo frets, three-ply mint green pick guard, American Vintage Telecaster bridge with threaded saddles, and American Vintage tuning machines. Includes black textured vinyl hard-shell case with red interior.
